1.2 Item Response Theory (IRT) Əsasları

1.2.1 IRT Nədir və Klassik Test Nəzəriyyəsindən Fərqləri

Item Response Theory (IRT) test nəticələrinin latent trait (gizli xüsusiyyət) və item parametrləri əsasında modelləşdirilməsi metodudur. Classical Test Theory (CTT)-dən əsas fərqləri:

CTT vs IRT Müqayisəsi:

CTT: X = T + E
IRT: P(X=1|θ) = f(θ, a, b, c)

Burada: - X = müşahidə edilən bal - T = həqiqi bal - E = xəta - θ (theta) = şəxsin qabiliyyət səviyyəsi - a = diskriminasiya parametri - b = çətinlik parametri - c = təsadüfi doğru parametri

1.2.2 Əsas IRT Modelləri

Əsas IRT Modellərinin Müqayisəsi
Model Parametr_Sayı Tənlik İstifadə_Sahəsi Xüsusiyyət
1PL (Rasch) 1 (b) exp(θ-b)/(1+exp(θ-b)) Sadə testlər Bərabər diskriminasiya
2PL 2 (a, b) exp(a(θ-b))/(1+exp(a(θ-b))) Ümumi məqsəd Dəyişən diskriminasiya
3PL 3 (a, b, c) c + (1-c)exp(a(θ-b))/(1+exp(a(θ-b))) Çoxseçimli testlər Təsadüfi doğru
4PL 4 (a, b, c, d) c + (d-c)exp(a(θ-b))/(1+exp(a(θ-b))) Təkmil analizlər Yuxarı asimptot

1.3.2 IRT Funksiyaları və Yardımçı Kodlar

# IRT model fit funksiyası
fit_irt_models <- function(data, models = c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL")) {
  results <- list()
  
  for (model in models) {
    tryCatch({
      if (model == "1PL") {
        fit <- ltm::rasch(data)
        results[[model]] <- fit
      } else if (model == "2PL") {
        fit <- ltm::ltm(data ~ z1)
        results[[model]] <- fit
      } else if (model == "3PL") {
        fit <- ltm::tpm(data)
        results[[model]] <- fit
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Xəta", model, "modelində:", e$message, "\n")
      results[[model]] <- NULL
    })
  }
  
  return(results)
}

# IRT parametrlərini çıxarma funksiyası
extract_irt_parameters <- function(fit_object, model_type) {
  if (is.null(fit_object)) return(NULL)
  
  tryCatch({
    if (model_type == "1PL") {
      params <- coef(fit_object)
      result <- data.frame(
        item = rownames(params),
        difficulty = -params[,1],  # Rasch modelində b parametri
        discrimination = 1,        # Rasch modelində a=1
        guessing = 0              # Rasch modelində c=0
      )
    } else if (model_type == "2PL") {
      params <- coef(fit_object)
      result <- data.frame(
        item = rownames(params),
        discrimination = params[,1],
        difficulty = -params[,2]/params[,1],
        guessing = 0
      )
    } else if (model_type == "3PL") {
      params <- coef(fit_object)
      result <- data.frame(
        item = rownames(params),
        discrimination = params[,1],
        difficulty = -params[,2]/params[,1],
        guessing = params[,3]
      )
    }
    
    return(result)
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Parametr çıxarma xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# IRT ability estimation funksiyası
estimate_abilities <- function(data, fit_object, model_type) {
  tryCatch({
    if (model_type %in% c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL")) {
      abilities <- factor.scores(fit_object, resp.patterns = data)
      return(abilities$score.dat$z1)
    }
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Ability estimation xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(rep(NA, nrow(data)))
  })
}

# Model fit statistikları
calculate_model_fit <- function(fit_object, data, model_type) {
  tryCatch({
    # AIC və BIC
    aic_val <- AIC(fit_object)
    bic_val <- BIC(fit_object)
    
    # Log-likelihood
    loglik_val <- logLik(fit_object)
    
    # Item fit statistics (basit versiya)
    n_items <- ncol(data)
    n_params <- switch(model_type,
                      "1PL" = n_items,
                      "2PL" = 2 * n_items,
                      "3PL" = 3 * n_items)
    
    result <- list(
      AIC = aic_val,
      BIC = bic_val,
      logLik = as.numeric(loglik_val),
      n_params = n_params,
      n_items = n_items
    )
    
    return(result)
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Model fit hesablama xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# Test Characteristic Curve hesablama
calculate_tcc <- function(fit_object, model_type, theta_range = seq(-4, 4, 0.1)) {
  tryCatch({
    if (model_type %in% c("1PL", "2PL", "3PL")) {
      tcc_data <- data.frame(
        theta = theta_range,
        expected_score = NA
      )
      
      # Hər theta səviyyəsi üçün gözlənilən balı hesabla
      for (i in 1:length(theta_range)) {
        theta_val <- theta_range[i]
        # Sadələşdirilmiş TCC hesablaması
        probs <- predict(fit_object, newdata = data.frame(z1 = theta_val))
        tcc_data$expected_score[i] <- sum(probs, na.rm = TRUE)
      }
      
      return(tcc_data)
    }
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("TCC hesablama xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# Sürətli statistika funksiyası (yenidən)
quick_stats <- function(scores, name = "Test") {
  list(
    name = name,
    n = length(scores),
    mean = round(mean(scores, na.rm = TRUE), 2),
    sd = round(sd(scores, na.rm = TRUE), 2),
    min = min(scores, na.rm = TRUE),
    max = max(scores, na.rm = TRUE),
    reliability = ifelse(length(scores) > 10, round(psych::alpha(as.matrix(scores))$total$std.alpha, 3), NA)
  )
}

2.1.1 3PL Modeli ilə Cavab Simulyasiyası

# 3PL model funksiyası
prob_3pl <- function(theta, a, b, c) {
  exp_term <- exp(a * (theta - b))
  prob <- c + (1 - c) * exp_term / (1 + exp_term)
  return(prob)
}

# Form 1 cavablarının simulyasiyası
form1_responses <- matrix(0, nrow = n_persons, ncol = n_items_form1)
for (i in 1:n_persons) {
  for (j in 1:n_items_form1) {
    prob <- prob_3pl(abilities_form1[i], form1_discrimination[j], 
                     form1_difficulty[j], form1_guessing[j])
    form1_responses[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
  }
}

# Form 2 cavablarının simulyasiyası
form2_responses <- matrix(0, nrow = n_persons, ncol = n_items_form2)
for (i in 1:n_persons) {
  for (j in 1:n_items_form2) {
    prob <- prob_3pl(abilities_form2[i], form2_discrimination[j], 
                     form2_difficulty[j], form2_guessing[j])
    form2_responses[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
  }
}

4 IRT-Based Equating Metodları

4.1 Concurrent Calibration Metodu

cat("=== Concurrent Calibration IRT Equating ===\n")
## === Concurrent Calibration IRT Equating ===
# Ümumi itemləri birləşdir (concurrent calibration)
if (n_common > 0 && !is.null(form1_params) && !is.null(form2_params)) {
  
  # Anchor itemlərin parametrlərini birləşdir
  anchor_items_f1 <- form1_responses[, 1:n_common]
  anchor_items_f2 <- form2_responses[, 1:n_common]
  
  # Bütün məlumatları birləşdir (concurrent design simulation)
  combined_anchor_data <- rbind(anchor_items_f1, anchor_items_f2)
  
  cat("Concurrent calibration aparılır...\n")
  concurrent_model <- tryCatch({
    ltm::ltm(combined_anchor_data ~ z1)
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Concurrent model xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
  
  if (!is.null(concurrent_model)) {
    concurrent_params <- extract_irt_parameters(concurrent_model, "2PL")
    
    if (!is.null(concurrent_params)) {
      cat("✅ Concurrent calibration uğurla tamamlandı\n")
      
      # Concurrent parametrlər
      cat("\n=== Concurrent Calibration Parametrləri ===\n")
      kable(head(concurrent_params, 10),
            caption = "Concurrent Calibration IRT Parametrləri",
            align = "c", digits = 3)
      
      # Form 1 və Form 2 ability estimation
      abilities_f1_concurrent <- estimate_abilities(anchor_items_f1, concurrent_model, "2PL")
      abilities_f2_concurrent <- estimate_abilities(anchor_items_f2, concurrent_model, "2PL")
      
      # IRT-based raw score conversion
      # Form 1 raw scores -> theta -> Form 2 raw scores
      
      # TCC hesablama
      tcc_f1 <- calculate_tcc(form1_models[[best_model_f1]], best_model_f1)
      tcc_f2 <- calculate_tcc(form2_models[[best_model_f2]], best_model_f2)
      
      if (!is.null(tcc_f1) && !is.null(tcc_f2)) {
        # Simplified IRT equating function
        irt_equate_f1_to_f2 <- function(raw_score_f1) {
          # Raw score -> theta (via interpolation)
          if (is.na(raw_score_f1) || raw_score_f1 < 0 || raw_score_f1 > n_items_form1) {
            return(NA)
          }
          
          # Find corresponding theta for this raw score in Form 1
          theta_estimate <- (raw_score_f1 / n_items_form1 - 0.5) * 4  # Simple linear mapping
          
          # Find expected raw score in Form 2 for this theta
          if (!is.null(tcc_f2) && nrow(tcc_f2) > 0) {
            closest_idx <- which.min(abs(tcc_f2$theta - theta_estimate))
            expected_f2 <- tcc_f2$expected_score[closest_idx]
            return(expected_f2)
          } else {
            # Alternative: simple linear scaling
            return(raw_score_f1 * mean(form2_raw_scores) / mean(form1_raw_scores))
          }
        }
        
        # Form 1 raw scores-u Form 2-yə çevir
        form1_to_form2_irt <- sapply(form1_raw_scores[1:100], irt_equate_f1_to_f2)
        
        # IRT equating nəticələri
        irt_equating_sample <- data.frame(
          Person = 1:min(100, length(form1_raw_scores)),
          Raw_Score_F1 = form1_raw_scores[1:min(100, length(form1_raw_scores))],
          IRT_Equated_F2 = round(form1_to_form2_irt, 1),
          Actual_F2 = form2_raw_scores[1:min(100, length(form2_raw_scores))],
          Difference = round(form1_to_form2_irt - form2_raw_scores[1:min(100, length(form2_raw_scores))], 1)
        )
        
        cat("\n=== IRT-Based Equating Nəticələri (İlk 12 şəxs) ===\n")
        kable(head(irt_equating_sample, 12),
              caption = "Form 1 → Form 2 IRT Equating",
              align = "c")
        
        # IRT equating keyfiyyəti
        valid_indices <- !is.na(form1_to_form2_irt)
        if (sum(valid_indices) > 0) {
          irt_rmse <- sqrt(mean((form1_to_form2_irt[valid_indices] - 
                                form2_raw_scores[valid_indices])^2, na.rm = TRUE))
          irt_mae <- mean(abs(form1_to_form2_irt[valid_indices] - 
                             form2_raw_scores[valid_indices]), na.rm = TRUE)
          irt_bias <- mean(form1_to_form2_irt[valid_indices] - 
                          form2_raw_scores[valid_indices], na.rm = TRUE)
          irt_correlation <- cor(form1_to_form2_irt[valid_indices], 
                                form2_raw_scores[valid_indices], use = "complete.obs")
          
          cat("\n=== IRT Equating Keyfiyyət Göstəriciləri ===\n")
          cat("RMSE:", round(irt_rmse, 3), "\n")
          cat("MAE:", round(irt_mae, 3), "\n")
          cat("Bias:", round(irt_bias, 3), "\n")
          cat("Correlation:", round(irt_correlation, 3), "\n")
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

  # Mean-Mean linking metodu
  cat("Mean-Mean linking metodu tətbiq edilir...\n")
  
  # Anchor itemlərin orta parametrləri
  anchor_mean_diff_f1 <- mean(form1_params$difficulty[1:n_common], na.rm = TRUE)
  anchor_mean_diff_f2 <- mean(form2_params$difficulty[1:n_common], na.rm = TRUE)

  anchor_mean_disc_f2 <- mean(form2_params$discrimination[1:n_common], na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # Linking constants (A və B)
  A_constant <- anchor_mean_disc_f1 / anchor_mean_disc_f2
  B_constant <- anchor_mean_diff_f1 - A_constant * anchor_mean_diff_f2
  
  cat("A constant (slope):", round(A_constant, 4), "\n")
  cat("B constant (intercept):", round(B_constant, 4), "\n")
  
  # Form 2 parametrlərini Form 1 scaləsinə çevir
  form2_params_linked <- form2_params
  form2_params_linked$difficulty <- A_constant * form2_params$difficulty + B_constant
  form2_params_linked$discrimination <- form2_params$discrimination / A_constant
  
  # Linking nəticələrinin müqayisəsi
  linking_comparison <- data.frame(
    Item = paste0("Item", 1:min(n_common, 8)),
    Original_F1_Diff = round(form1_params$difficulty[1:min(n_common, 8)], 3),

                               form2_params$difficulty[1:min(n_common, 8)], 3),
    Linked_Difference = round(form1_params$difficulty[1:min(n_common, 8)] - 
                             form2_params_linked$difficulty[1:min(n_common, 8)], 3)
  )
  
  cat("\n=== Mean-Mean Linking Nəticələri ===\n")
  kable(linking_comparison,
        caption = "Anchor İtemlərin Linking Öncəsi və Sonrası Parametrləri",
        align = "c")

  linking_rmse_disc <- sqrt(mean((form1_params$discrimination[1:n_common] - 
                                 form2_params_linked$discrimination[1:n_common])^2, na.rm = TRUE))

  anchor_sd_diff_f2 <- sd(form2_params$difficulty[1:n_common], na.rm = TRUE)

cat("=== Kernel Equating Metodu ===\n")
## === Kernel Equating Metodu ===
# Kernel equating R-də equate paketi ilə
tryCatch({
  # Score distributions
  form1_score_dist <- table(form1_raw_scores)
  form2_score_dist <- table(form2_raw_scores)
  
  # Kernel equating preparation
  # Convert to required format for equate package
  form1_freqtab <- data.frame(
    score = as.numeric(names(form1_score_dist)),
    freq = as.numeric(form1_score_dist)
  )
  
  form2_freqtab <- data.frame(
    score = as.numeric(names(form2_score_dist)),
    freq = as.numeric(form2_score_dist)
  )
  
  cat("Form 1 score distribution:\n")
  cat("Min score:", min(form1_freqtab$score), "Max score:", max(form1_freqtab$score), "\n")
  cat("Form 2 score distribution:\n")
  cat("Min score:", min(form2_freqtab$score), "Max score:", max(form2_freqtab$score), "\n")
  
  # Kernel equating using different bandwidths
  kernel_bandwidths <- c(0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0)
  kernel_results <- list()
  
  for (h in kernel_bandwidths) {
    tryCatch({
      # Create frequency tables in proper format
      x_scores <- form1_raw_scores
      y_scores <- form2_raw_scores
      
      # Simple kernel equating implementation
      kernel_eq <- data.frame(
        raw_score = 0:max(c(form1_raw_scores, form2_raw_scores)),
        equated_score = NA
      )
      
      for (score in kernel_eq$raw_score) {
        # Gaussian kernel smoothing
        weights_x <- exp(-((x_scores - score)^2) / (2 * h^2))
        weights_x <- weights_x / sum(weights_x)
        
        # Percentile rank estimation
        pr_x <- sum(weights_x * (x_scores <= score))
        
        # Find corresponding score in Y distribution
        weights_y <- exp(-((y_scores - quantile(y_scores, pr_x, na.rm = TRUE))^2) / (2 * h^2))
        weights_y <- weights_y / sum(weights_y)
        
        equated_y <- sum(weights_y * y_scores)
        kernel_eq$equated_score[kernel_eq$raw_score == score] <- equated_y
      }
      
      kernel_results[[paste0("h_", h)]] <- kernel_eq
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Kernel equating xətası (h =", h, "):", e$message, "\n")
    })
  }
  
  # Kernel equating nəticələrinin müqayisəsi
  if (length(kernel_results) > 0) {
    sample_scores <- seq(5, 35, 5)
    kernel_comparison <- data.frame(
      Raw_Score = sample_scores
    )
    
    for (h_name in names(kernel_results)) {
      h_val <- as.numeric(sub("h_", "", h_name))
      equated_vals <- sapply(sample_scores, function(s) {
        idx <- which.min(abs(kernel_results[[h_name]]$raw_score - s))
        return(round(kernel_results[[h_name]]$equated_score[idx], 1))
      })
      kernel_comparison[[paste0("h_", h_val)]] <- equated_vals
    }
    
    cat("\n=== Kernel Equating Nəticələri (Müxtəlif Bandwidth) ===\n")
    kable(kernel_comparison,
          caption = "Kernel Equating - Bandwidth Müqayisəsi",
          align = "c")
  }
  
}, error = function(e) {
  cat("Kernel equating ümumi xətası:", e$message, "\n")
})

5.2 Bootstrap Confidence Intervals

cat("=== Bootstrap Confidence Intervals ===\n")
## === Bootstrap Confidence Intervals ===
# Bootstrap equating function
bootstrap_irt_equating <- function(form1_data, form2_data, n_boot = 200) {
  n1 <- nrow(form1_data)
  n2 <- nrow(form2_data)
  
  boot_results <- matrix(NA, nrow = n_boot, ncol = 5)
  colnames(boot_results) <- c("score_10", "score_20", "score_25", "score_30", "score_35")
  
  test_scores <- c(10, 20, 25, 30, 35)
  
  for (b in 1:n_boot) {
    tryCatch({
      # Bootstrap samples
      boot_idx1 <- sample(1:n1, n1, replace = TRUE)
      boot_idx2 <- sample(1:n2, n2, replace = TRUE)
      
      boot_form1 <- form1_data[boot_idx1, ]
      boot_form2 <- form2_data[boot_idx2, ]
      
      boot_scores1 <- rowSums(boot_form1)
      boot_scores2 <- rowSums(boot_form2)
      
      # Simple linear equating for bootstrap
      mean1 <- mean(boot_scores1)
      mean2 <- mean(boot_scores2)
      sd1 <- sd(boot_scores1)
      sd2 <- sd(boot_scores2)
      
      slope <- sd2 / sd1
      intercept <- mean2 - slope * mean1
      
      # Equate test scores
      equated_scores <- intercept + slope * test_scores
      boot_results[b, ] <- equated_scores
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      # Skip this bootstrap iteration if error
    })
  }
  
  return(boot_results)
}

8.2 Test Information Functions

# Test Information Function hesablama və vizualizasiya
if (!is.null(form1_params) && !is.null(form2_params)) {
  
  theta_range <- seq(-3, 3, 0.1)
  
  # Form 1 Test Information
  form1_info <- numeric(length(theta_range))
  for (i in 1:length(theta_range)) {
    theta_val <- theta_range[i]
    item_info_sum <- 0
    
    for (j in 1:nrow(form1_params)) {
      if (!is.na(form1_params$difficulty[j]) && !is.na(form1_params$discrimination[j])) {
        a_val <- form1_params$discrimination[j]
        b_val <- form1_params$difficulty[j]
        c_val <- ifelse(is.na(form1_params$guessing[j]), 0, form1_params$guessing[j])
        
        # 3PL item information
        prob <- c_val + (1 - c_val) * exp(a_val * (theta_val - b_val)) / 
                (1 + exp(a_val * (theta_val - b_val)))
        
        if (c_val == 0) {
          # 2PL item information
          item_info <- a_val^2 * prob * (1 - prob)
        } else {
          # 3PL item information
          item_info <- a_val^2 * ((prob - c_val)^2 / ((1 - c_val)^2 * prob)) * (1 - prob)
        }
        
        item_info_sum <- item_info_sum + item_info
      }
    }
    form1_info[i] <- item_info_sum
  }
  
  # Form 2 Test Information
  form2_info <- numeric(length(theta_range))
  for (i in 1:length(theta_range)) {
    theta_val <- theta_range[i]
    item_info_sum <- 0
    
    for (j in 1:nrow(form2_params)) {
      if (!is.na(form2_params$difficulty[j]) && !is.na(form2_params$discrimination[j])) {
        a_val <- form2_params$discrimination[j]
        b_val <- form2_params$difficulty[j]
        c_val <- ifelse(is.na(form2_params$guessing[j]), 0, form2_params$guessing[j])
        
        prob <- c_val + (1 - c_val) * exp(a_val * (theta_val - b_val)) / 
                (1 + exp(a_val * (theta_val - b_val)))
        
        if (c_val == 0) {
          item_info <- a_val^2 * prob * (1 - prob)
        } else {
          item_info <- a_val^2 * ((prob - c_val)^2 / ((1 - c_val)^2 * prob)) * (1 - prob)
        }
        
        item_info_sum <- item_info_sum + item_info
      }
    }
    form2_info[i] <- item_info_sum
  }
  
  # Test Information Functions plot
  par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
  
  plot(theta_range, form1_info, type = "l", col = colors_custom[1], lwd = 3,
       main = "Test Information Functions", xlab = "Ability (θ)", ylab = "Information",
       ylim = c(0, max(c(form1_info, form2_info), na.rm = TRUE)))
  lines(theta_range, form2_info, col = colors_custom[2], lwd = 3)
  legend("topright", c("Form 1", "Form 2"), col = colors_custom[1:2], lwd = 3)
  grid()
  
  # Standard Error of Measurement
  form1_sem <- 1 / sqrt(pmax(form1_info, 0.01))  # Minimum info to avoid division by 0
  form2_sem <- 1 / sqrt(pmax(form2_info, 0.01))
  
  plot(theta_range, form1_sem, type = "l", col = colors_custom[1], lwd = 3,
       main = "Standard Error of Measurement", xlab = "Ability (θ)", ylab = "SEM",
       ylim = c(0, max(c(form1_sem, form2_sem), na.rm = TRUE)))
  lines(theta_range, form2_sem, col = colors_custom[2], lwd = 3)
  legend("topright", c("Form 1", "Form 2"), col = colors_custom[1:2], lwd = 3)
  grid()
  
  # Information summary
  info_summary <- data.frame(
    Form = c("Form 1", "Form 2"),
    Max_Information = c(round(max(form1_info, na.rm = TRUE), 2), 
                       round(max(form2_info, na.rm = TRUE), 2)),
    Theta_at_Max = c(round(theta_range[which.max(form1_info)], 2),
                    round(theta_range[which.max(form2_info)], 2)),
    Min_SEM = c(round(min(form1_sem, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
               round(min(form2_sem, na.rm = TRUE), 3)),
    Mean_Information = c(round(mean(form1_info, na.rm = TRUE), 2),
                        round(mean(form2_info, na.rm = TRUE), 2))
  )
  
  cat("\n=== Test Information Statistikaları ===\n")
  kable(info_summary,
        caption = "Test Information və SEM Təhlili",
        align = "c")
}

  • ✅ IRT parametrlərinin interpretasiyası
  • ✅ Concurrent və separate calibration metodları
  • ✅ Modern equating metodları (Kernel, Bootstrap)
  • ✅ Metodların müqayisəli analizi

11.3.2 📊 Praktiki Tətbiq

  • IRT modellərinin fit edilməsi (1PL, 2PL, 3PL)
  • Parametr çıxarma və linking analizi
  • Test Information Function hesablaması
  • Bootstrap güven aralıqlarının qurulması
  • Keyfiyyət göstəricilərinin qiymətləndirilməsi

11.3.3 🔍 Əsas Tapıntılar

  • IRT metodları klassik metodlardan daha çevik
  • Böyük nümunə və ekspert bilgisi tələb edir
  • Model seçimi və fit yoxlaması kritikdir
  • Bootstrap analizi sabitliyi göstərir

11.3.4 📚 Növbəti Addımlar

  • Multidimensional IRT öyrənmək
  • DIF analizi metodları
  • Computer Adaptive Testing
  • Real məlumatlarla təcrübə
